1 B. The post-installation inspection shall be conducted by a
2 qualified engineer or inspector approved by the Department to ensure
3 compliance with industry standards, including, but not limited to:
4 1. Structural integrity under expected loads;
5 2. Proper bedding and backfill placement;
6 3. Joint integrity and alignment; and
7 4. Absence of significant defects such as cracks, deformations,
8 or separations.
9 C. The contractor shall bear the cost of the post-installation
10 inspection and any corrective measures required to meet the
11 Departmentâ€™s standards. If a storm pipe fails the post-installation
12 inspection, the contractor shall take corrective action, which may
13 include removal and replacement, reinforcement, or other remediation
14 as directed by the Department.
15 D. The Oklahoma Department of Transportation shall promulgate
16 rules necessary to implement and enforce the provisions of this
17 section, including, but not limited to, specifications for
18 inspections, testing protocols, and qualifications for inspectors.
19 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
